  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers just triggered a massive GEX surge (185-299% in 1-5 minutes) as SPX broke above the 6577 flip strike into PIN regime, forcing them to sell delta into strength as they're now long gamma. With spot at 6566 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6550 and the towering +49.7B wall at 6580, dealers are providing stabilizing flow - they'll aggressively buy any dip toward 6550 and sell any rally toward the 6580 resistance wall.\n\nThe thick positive gamma walls stacked from 6570-6590 create a natural trading range where mean reversion should dominate, with 6580 acting as the primary resistance level where dealer selling pressure intensifies most.",
